&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Given Data:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Votes secured by B = 16,200&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Percentage of votes by which B defeated A = 8%&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Concept:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The total number of votes can be calculated considering that B won by 8% of total votes. Then, the votes that A received can be derived, and the difference between votes of A and B can be calculated.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Calculation:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Total number of votes be 100%&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; Votes secured by A be x%&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;&amp;rArr; Votes secured by B&amp;nbsp;be (x + 8)%&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;According to question&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;&amp;rArr; Total votes = x + x + 8 = 100&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;&amp;rArr; 2x = 92&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;&amp;rArr; x = 46%&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;&amp;rArr; x + 8 = 54%&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;Votes secured by B&amp;nbsp;be (x + 8)% = 54% = 16200&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;&amp;rArr; 1 % = 300&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;&amp;rArr; 8% = 2400&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; Difference between votes of A and B = Votes secured by B - Votes secured by A = 8% = 2400&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Therefore, the difference in votes between A and B is 2400 votes.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Given:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The numerator of a fraction is decreased by 25%&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The denominator is increased by 25%&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Concept:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The percentage decrease in the value of the fraction is given by Original fraction - New fraction/Original fraction &amp;times; 100.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Solution:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; New fraction = (1 - 0.25)/(1 + 0.25) = 0.75/1.25 = 0.6 (Consider original fraction as 1 for simplification)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; Percentage decrease = (1 - 0.6)/1 &amp;times; 100 = 40%&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hence, the new fraction is 40% less than the original fraction.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Given:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Initial increase = 15%&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Decrease = 25%&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Concept:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Successive percentage change&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Solution:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; The net percentage change for two successive changes a and b is given by a + b + ab/100&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; Substitute a = 15 and b = -25 (decrease is taken as negative)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;&amp;rArr; 15 - 25 - 375/100 = - 13.75%&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Therefore, there is a 13.75% decrease in the salary.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Given data:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Candidate A&amp;#39;s vote share = 42%&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Difference in votes between candidates A and B = 8000 votes&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Concept:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The difference between the votes of the two candidates can be expressed as a percentage of the total votes.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Solution:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Candidate B&amp;#39;s vote share = 100% - 42% = 58%&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The difference between the vote shares of B and A = 58% - 42% = 16%&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; 16% of Total votes = 8000 votes&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We can find the total number of votes (T) from this equation&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; T = 8000 / (16 / 100)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;&amp;rArr;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;T = 8000 &amp;times; 100 / 16&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; T = 50000&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Therefore&amp;nbsp;the total number of votes is 50000.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Given:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Expenditure = 68% of his monthly income.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Savings =&amp;nbsp;Rs. 14,720&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Concept used:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Income = savings + expenditure&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Calculation:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;His total income is 100%&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;He spends 68%&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So he saves 100 - 68 = 32%&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So the value of 32 % = 14720&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So the value of 68% = (14720 / 32)&amp;times; 68&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;rArr; Rs 31,280&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;there4; The correct option is 3&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
